Chairman of the Board of Directors of Arabian Gulf Oil Company, ‘Mohamad Bin Shatwan’, discussed with the Director of Maintenance Department of the German Siemens company, “Yusuf Al-Marimi” prospects for joint cooperation, in the context of encouraging the return of large companies to work at the sites of the Gulf Company. During the meeting, they discussed the resumption of Siemens international activity, especially with regard to the maintenance of gas controls in the Nafora oil field, with confirmation of cooperation between the Gulf Company and the German company, which is the largest European company in the field of modern electrical and electronic engineering.